This paper deals with sentiment analysis in Twitter, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also evaluates the performance of classification algorithms, which falls under machine learning (ML) and data mining (DM), making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of graphs, which is a topic in network science and social network analysis, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses lexicon-based approaches, which is a topic in natural language processing and computational linguistics, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category.
